          "Do the homework that produces specifics. Read the actual job description and name a responsibility back to them. Read the engineering blog, recent talks, or the public API and SDK docs and reference one concrete thing. Check what the company shipped recently. For Treasure Data you can say: 'The Staff Fullstack role on the realtime and personalization side is almost exactly the shape of system I've been building, low-latency event processing feeding a personalization layer, and I want to do that as a technical anchor rather than as one feature among many.' For Toast: 'You run a platform that thousands of restaurants and many integration partners depend on, and reliability-at-scale for external consumers is the problem I've spent the last few years on.'",
