          "An interviewer may ask 'why do transformers need positional encoding' (because self-attention is order-agnostic) and 'when would you pick encoder-only vs decoder-only.' Answer the second by task shape: encoder-only for understanding tasks with the full input visible (classification, embeddings, reranking), decoder-only for generation, encoder-decoder for explicit input-to-output transduction. Note that the industry has converged on decoder-only for general-purpose LLMs because it scales simply and handles most tasks via prompting."
