          "Re-ranking is a second, more expensive scoring pass over the top candidates. The key architectural distinction to name: a bi-encoder (the embedding model) encodes query and document separately, so it is fast and precomputable but coarse; a cross-encoder feeds the query and a candidate together through one transformer and outputs a direct relevance score, which is far more accurate but cannot be precomputed. The standard pattern is retrieve broadly (say top 50 to 100 via ANN plus BM25), then cross-encode those down to the top 3 to 8 that actually enter the prompt. On AWS, the Bedrock Rerank API (launched at re:Invent 2024) offers Amazon Rerank 1.0 and Cohere Rerank 3.5, both cross-encoders, and OpenSearch can call them in its search pipeline.",
