          "Anchor it in things you have actually built so your answer carries authority. Your SQS/Lambda/DynamoDB batch system is a ready-made template for any ingestion, fan-out, or throttling design: explain dead-letter queues, visibility timeouts, idempotency keys to make retries safe, and backpressure. Your WAF-hardened API with 40+ partners maps directly onto multi-tenant API design: rate limiting, auth (API keys versus OAuth/JWT), per-tenant quotas, and blast-radius isolation. Your Bedrock RAG pipeline is current and on-trend given Autodesk's AI-native push, so be ready to discuss chunking, embedding storage and vector search, retrieval quality, latency, and cost controls. It is worth knowing Autodesk runs Bedrock in production (it powers Autodesk Assistant, their agentic AI), so naming Bedrock by name lands. Always close with explicit trade-offs: cost versus latency, strong versus eventual consistency, build versus managed.",
